Vasco Chaya LIFESTYLE WRITER chayav@dailynews.co.zw UNITED Kingdom- based playwright Enisia Mashusha is collaborating with arts industry gurus to launch an online dance show to promote women dancers in the country. The all-female dance show, dubbed WoKadzi, is pencilled for August. WoKadzi will be directed by veteran actress Eunice Tava. It will run under the theme No to Gender-Based Violence during this time of Covid-19.  The show comes at a time when women pressure groups such as the Musasa Project have recorded over 1 000 cases of gender-based violence during the national coronavirus lockdown period alone.  googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1588599181508-1'); }); Mashusha, who also runs another online television show The A-List, made her name in showbiz as the founder of the famed Mambokadzi — the award-winning arts group which was the catalyst of the dance group craze that swept through local showbiz between 2005 and 2010. Under her leadership, the group made a huge impact on both local and international platforms. Mashusha remains an inspirational figure on the local dance scene.